Replace shipped `dontAsk` permission default with deny+ask config

Both `.claude.json` (root) and `rust/.claw.json` shipped with
`{"permissions": {"defaultMode": "dontAsk"}}`, which the runtime resolves to
`ResolvedPermissionMode::DangerFullAccess` (runtime/src/config.rs:858). Every
tool in `mvp_tool_specs` requires `DangerFullAccess`, so under the shipped
default every tool call satisfies the policy gate trivially — bash and file
writes execute without prompting.

Replace with `defaultMode: "default"` (resolves to ReadOnly), an explicit
deny list for the highest-leverage shell commands, and an `ask` catch-all so
any uncovered Bash invocation surfaces for confirmation rather than running
silently.

`.claude.json` is included so opening the repo in Claude Code itself doesn't
also inherit the permissive default. `rust/.claw.json` is the file the `claw`
binary reads when started from the workspace.
---
diff --git a/.claude.json b/.claude.json
--- a/.claude.json
+++ b/.claude.json
@@ -1,5 +1,14 @@
 {
   "permissions": {
-    "defaultMode": "dontAsk"
+    "defaultMode": "default",
+    "deny": [
+      "Bash(curl:*)",
+      "Bash(wget:*)",
+      "Bash(sudo:*)",
+      "Bash(rm:*)"
+    ],
+    "ask": [
+      "Bash"
+    ]
   }
 }
diff --git a/rust/.claw.json b/rust/.claw.json
--- a/rust/.claw.json
+++ b/rust/.claw.json
@@ -1,5 +1,14 @@
 {
   "permissions": {
-    "defaultMode": "dontAsk"
+    "defaultMode": "default",
+    "deny": [
+      "Bash(curl:*)",
+      "Bash(wget:*)",
+      "Bash(sudo:*)",
+      "Bash(rm:*)"
+    ],
+    "ask": [
+      "Bash"
+    ]
   }
 }
